column5: Patent of nobility for Carl Caspar Siebold (1801) In 1801, Carl Caspar (now von) Siebold was ennobled by the Emperor for his services to the wounded soldiers after the battle of W\'fcrzburg in September, 1796. Note, in the blazon, the hand holding a lancet. Siebold archives Mittelbiberach/ Burg Brandenstein.
